	<div class="w-full md:w-1/2">
		<p>
			Being part of a project-based learning cohort is quite different from regular courses. Students who derive
			the
			greatest
			benefit from the STEM program are self-starters, show commitment, and work well in groups. Students wishing
			to
			enter the
			STEM program must be Templeton students. Registration information for joining the Templeton family can be
			found
			at the
			VSB website. Enrollment in Templeton STEM is limited and a separate application is required, using the form
			below.
		</p>

		<ul class="nav nav-tabs pt-16">
			<li class="active menus">
				<a class="active" data-toggle="tab" href="#menu1">Grade 8</a>
			</li>
			<li class="menus">
				<a data-toggle="tab" href="#menu2">Grade 9 - 12</a>
			</li>
		</ul>

		<div class="tab-content h-80 lg:h-64">
			<div id="menu1" class="tab-pane fade in active show">
				<p class="px-2 py-2">Students can apply to be in a STEM 8 cohort using the Templeton STEM application
					form. The deadline
					for
					application is
					the last day of school in December. In cases where there are more applicants than spaces, selections
					are
					made by
					lottery. Notification of acceptance is given in the last week of February.</p>

			</div>
			<div id="menu2" class="tab-pane fade">
				<p class="px-2 py-2">Where space permits, Templeton students may join the STEM program in any grade by
					contacting their
					grade
					level
					counsellor. In
					the situation where a cohort is over-subscribed, placements will be made by lottery to students who
					have a
					high degree
					of initiative, perseverance in the face of failure, and commitment to growth as a learner.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

